- Use docstrings for all functions and classes, following the PEP 257 conventions.
- Document parameters, return types, and exceptions in docstrings.
- Utilize type hints for better clarity and type safety.
- Create a comprehensive README that includes project description, installation instructions, usage examples, and contribution guidelines.
- Leverage Pydantic's BaseModel for data validation and serialization, ensuring clear and structured data handling.
- Organize code into modules and packages for better maintainability and readability.